34:40.829 --> 34:42.370
You've had five days
at your home forge

34:42.414 --> 34:43.538
to work on your Viking swords,

34:43.582 --> 34:44.831
and we want to hear about it.

34:44.875 --> 34:46.208
We already know this is

34:46.251 --> 34:49.002
an incredibly
difficult sword to make.

34:49.046 --> 34:51.797
Gabe, tell us a little bit about
the construction of your sword.

34:51.840 --> 34:53.632
- Well, the sword I constructed

34:53.675 --> 34:57.636
<i> is actually a composite</i>
<i> of two bundles of cable.</i>

34:57.679 --> 35:00.722
<i> Most of the difficult</i>
<i> challenges went very well,</i>

35:00.766 --> 35:02.891
<i> and some of the small things</i>
<i> I had a little trouble with.</i>

35:02.935 --> 35:04.101
<i> But overall,</i>

35:04.144 --> 35:05.727
it went very well for me.

35:05.771 --> 35:07.104
- Clarence, how'd it go?

35:07.147 --> 35:08.146
- My sword should be called

35:08.190 --> 35:10.190
<i> Blood, Sweat, and Tears,</i>

35:10.234 --> 35:12.651
<i> 'cause I went through</i>
<i> plenty of that,</i>

35:12.694 --> 35:13.819
<i> enough for several people.</i>

35:13.862 --> 35:15.195
<i> It was a lot of struggle,</i>

35:15.239 --> 35:17.906
<i> but I put a sword together.</i>

35:17.950 --> 35:20.909
- Well, gentlemen, the road to
redemption is not an easy one.

35:20.953 --> 35:23.703
Your weapons will now be put
through a series of three tests.

35:23.747 --> 35:25.914
Up first, the sharpness test.

35:25.958 --> 35:27.624
Dave?

35:27.668 --> 35:30.210
- Gentlemen, to test
the sharpness of your blade,

35:30.254 --> 35:33.296
I will be cutting into
our cargo net here.

35:33.340 --> 35:35.674
Now, Gabe, you're up first.
Are you ready for this?

35:35.717 --> 35:38.510
- Definitely.
- All right.

35:38.554 --> 35:40.595
<i> - After previously being</i>
<i> eliminated in the first round,</i>

35:40.639 --> 35:43.181
<i> it feels very redeeming</i>
<i> to make it this far,</i>

35:43.225 --> 35:44.724
and to have been so low,

35:44.768 --> 35:49.062
to come so high
just feels exhilarating.

35:49.106 --> 35:50.647
<i> I'm very confident my blade</i>

35:50.691 --> 35:53.066
<i> is gonna slice</i>
<i> right through the cargo net.</i>

35:53.110 --> 35:58.488
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:59.533 --> 36:01.741
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:01.785 --> 36:03.034
- Well, Gabe, that blade made

36:03.078 --> 36:05.036
pretty short work
of the rope net.

36:05.080 --> 36:07.455
The weight overall
is a nice feel.

36:07.499 --> 36:09.291
Definitely did a good job.

36:09.334 --> 36:12.460
Definitely a sharp weapon
and felt good cutting.

36:12.504 --> 36:14.671
Nicely done, Gabe.
- Thank you.

36:14.715 --> 36:16.673
- All right, Clarence.
Your turn. Are you ready?

36:16.717 --> 36:17.966
- I'm ready.
- Okay.

36:18.010 --> 36:24.973
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:29.229 --> 36:30.645
All right.
So Clarence, a couple of things

36:30.689 --> 36:31.938
I really like about this blade:

36:31.982 --> 36:33.607
the weight is very nice,

36:33.650 --> 36:36.151
and the balance
is very well done.

36:36.195 --> 36:39.404
This big lip
in the handle, though,

36:39.448 --> 36:43.116
is really not very comfortable
on the hand.

36:43.160 --> 36:45.619
But your blade did well.

36:45.662 --> 36:48.371
It cut nicely.
Well done.

36:48.415 --> 36:50.665
So next up, gentlemen,
is the kill test,

36:50.709 --> 36:52.542
and for that,
I'll give you to Doug.

36:52.586 --> 36:55.629
- Bladesmiths, the Viking sword,
wielded by the hands

36:55.672 --> 36:57.547
of the feared Viking warriors,

36:57.591 --> 37:00.217
forged for one purpose:
kill the enemy.

37:00.260 --> 37:02.344
To see how lethal
your weapons are,

37:02.387 --> 37:04.179
I will take your Viking sword
and deliver killing blows

37:04.223 --> 37:05.972
on this ballistics dummy.

37:06.016 --> 37:08.099
Let's see what kind of damage
your weapon can do.

37:08.143 --> 37:09.476
Gabe, you're up first.
You ready?

37:09.519 --> 37:11.019
- I'm ready.
- Let's do this.

37:11.063 --> 37:17.984
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:28.705 --> 37:31.248
Okay, Gabe,
the handle is comfortable

37:31.291 --> 37:32.332
with the wrapping
that you did there.

37:32.376 --> 37:33.833
It feels good.

37:33.877 --> 37:35.627
As you can see, it lacerated

37:35.671 --> 37:37.629
the chest--
the chest cavity here,

37:37.673 --> 37:39.965
even took out some bones
of the ribs.

37:40.008 --> 37:43.051
It is sharp on both edges
and penetrated easily

37:43.095 --> 37:44.678
on this ballistics dummy,

37:44.721 --> 37:47.722
and most importantly,
it will kill.

37:47.766 --> 37:49.432
Good job.
- Thank you.

37:49.476 --> 37:51.226
- Clarence, you're up next.
Are you ready?

37:51.270 --> 37:52.727
- I'm ready.

37:52.771 --> 37:59.693
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:04.533 --> 38:07.534
- Okay, Clarence,
it feels good to wield.

38:07.577 --> 38:09.828
It's got great balance to it.

38:09.871 --> 38:12.038
The one thing
that it didn't do

38:12.082 --> 38:14.332
was cut cleanly

38:14.376 --> 38:16.001
through the ballistics dummy.

38:16.044 --> 38:17.877
It felt like
it was bouncing off,

38:17.921 --> 38:19.379
and I'm wondering ing
that's your edge geometry here,

38:19.423 --> 38:21.548
being thick
and the sharpness of your blade.

38:21.591 --> 38:24.092
But in the cuts that it did do,

38:24.136 --> 38:27.554
the weight did penetrate,
broke some bones.

38:27.597 --> 38:31.433
It penetrated on a deep
thrust coming out,

38:31.476 --> 38:34.185
and that would be
a very lethal wound,

38:34.229 --> 38:37.314
and your weapon will kill.

38:37.357 --> 38:39.858
All right. Bladesmiths,
next up is the strength test.

38:39.901 --> 38:41.443
Dave?

38:41.486 --> 38:43.194
- Now, the Viking sword
was commonly used

38:43.238 --> 38:44.779
in conjunction with a shield.

38:44.823 --> 38:46.865
So to test the strength
of your sword,

38:46.908 --> 38:50.035
I'm going to take four blows
into the wooden shield edges,

38:50.078 --> 38:52.620
two with either edge
of your blade.

38:52.664 --> 38:53.872
Gabe, you're up first.
Are you ready?

38:53.915 --> 38:55.332
- Yes, sir.
- All right.

38:55.375 --> 39:02.297
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:11.058 --> 39:12.599
All right, so Gabe,

39:12.642 --> 39:15.727
it's still in
the same shape it was in.

39:15.771 --> 39:18.021
That's good.
It's kept its straightness.

39:18.065 --> 39:20.190
It feels like your edge
held up really nicely.

39:20.233 --> 39:22.650
It definitely cut
into the shield good.

39:22.694 --> 39:24.444
Good job.
- Thank you.

39:24.488 --> 39:26.112
- All right, Clarence,
you're up.

39:26.156 --> 39:27.489
Are you ready?
- I'm ready.

39:27.532 --> 39:29.115
- Okay.

39:29.159 --> 39:30.867
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:30.911 --> 39:34.579
- Gabriel's sword is gorgeous,
of course.

39:34.623 --> 39:37.499
<i> But I actually like the way</i>
<i> my blade looks even more.</i>

39:37.542 --> 39:39.167
<i> The blade's gotten this far.</i>

39:39.211 --> 39:41.628
This is kind of
the moment of truth.

39:41.671 --> 39:44.714
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:50.722 --> 39:52.138
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:52.182 --> 39:53.473
- All right.
Clarence, you're up.

39:53.517 --> 39:54.808
Are you ready?
- I'm ready.

39:54.851 --> 39:56.184
- Okay.

39:56.228 --> 40:03.108
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:14.162 --> 40:18.206
Well, Clarence,
your edge held up nicely.

40:18.250 --> 40:22.585
That handle still, in my hand,
is still a bit of an issue.

40:22.629 --> 40:27.132
But swinging it, the weight
and the balance is really nice.

40:27.175 --> 40:31.094
All in all, well done.
- Thank you.

40:31.138 --> 40:32.387
<i> Now that the testing is over,</i>

40:32.431 --> 40:34.431
I'm glad my sword held up.

40:34.474 --> 40:36.516
<i> This is</i>
<i> a neck-and-neck situation,</i>

40:36.560 --> 40:40.562
<i> and who knows what</i>
<i> the judges' decision will be.</i>

40:40.605 --> 40:45.024
- Gabe, Clarence, your road
to redemption was a gauntlet.

40:45.068 --> 40:46.526
The judges have deliberated,

40:46.570 --> 40:48.611
and they've made
a final decision.

40:48.655 --> 40:51.406
Before that, they have
some feedback for both of you.

40:51.450 --> 40:53.783
Jason?

40:53.827 --> 40:55.160
- Gabe, a couple things

40:55.203 --> 40:56.911
that I really liked
about your sword:

40:56.955 --> 41:00.999
<i> one was that you chose</i>
<i> to use cable to make Damascus.</i>

41:01.042 --> 41:02.959
<i> But I also liked</i>
<i> the symmetry of the blade.</i>

41:03.003 --> 41:05.253
<i> I liked that you put</i>
<i> a fuller in the blade.</i>

41:05.297 --> 41:07.172
<i> I think the handle could've</i>
<i> been a little bit shorter,</i>

41:07.215 --> 41:09.716
but very well done.

41:09.759 --> 41:11.926
- Thank you.
- Clarence, the last time

41:11.970 --> 41:13.761
you were here,
you went out on round one

41:13.805 --> 41:15.305
because of a small crack
in your blade,

41:15.348 --> 41:17.056
a questionable quench.

41:17.100 --> 41:19.142
This time, you made it
all the way until the end.

41:19.186 --> 41:21.186
You brought us a sword
whose experience you've called,

41:21.229 --> 41:23.229
<i> "Blood, sweat, and tears."</i>

41:23.273 --> 41:26.316
<i> I think all the judges here</i>
<i>love the balance of your blade.</i>

41:26.359 --> 41:29.360
<i> The only issue:</i>
<i> in the kill test,</i>

41:29.404 --> 41:30.737
it actually bounced off

41:30.780 --> 41:32.363
<i> the ballistics dummy.</i>

41:32.407 --> 41:36.784
But overall, fantastic job.

41:36.828 --> 41:39.621
- The Forged in Fire
champion is...

41:39.664 --> 41:45.543
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:45.587 --> 41:46.836
Gabe.

41:46.880 --> 41:49.005
Congratulations.

41:49.049 --> 41:51.674
Clarence, your Viking sword
did not make the cut.

41:51.718 --> 41:53.635
Dave will explain.

41:53.678 --> 41:56.387
- Clarence, you've gone way
beyond redeeming yourself.

41:56.431 --> 41:58.681
<i> But what it came down</i>
<i> to was performance.</i>

41:58.725 --> 42:02.143
<i> Because of your edge geometry</i>
<i>and the sharpness of that edge,</i>

42:02.187 --> 42:03.228
<i> in our kill test,</i>

42:03.271 --> 42:04.854
it just underperformed,

42:04.898 --> 42:07.106
and that's why
we're letting you go.

42:07.150 --> 42:09.776
- Clarence, please,
surrender your weapon.

42:11.404 --> 42:13.488
<i> - The first time I competed,</i>

42:13.532 --> 42:16.449
I wound up out in round one.

42:16.493 --> 42:18.535
This time, I've made it through
to the finale.

42:18.578 --> 42:19.619
<i> So I may not be</i>

42:19.663 --> 42:21.162
a "Forged in Fire" champion,

42:21.206 --> 42:23.873
but I have proven to myself

42:23.917 --> 42:25.041
that I can go

42:25.085 --> 42:26.668
<i> much further than I thought.</i>

42:26.711 --> 42:27.961
So there'll be definitely

42:28.004 --> 42:31.130
lots more to look forward to.

42:31.174 --> 42:33.550
- Gabe, congratulations.

42:33.593 --> 42:35.635
You are
the "Forged in Fire" champion

42:35.679 --> 42:38.221
and will be receiving
that check for 10 grand.

42:38.265 --> 42:41.391
[applause]

42:41.434 --> 42:43.142
If that's not redemption,
I don't know what is, brother.

42:43.186 --> 42:45.728
- Oh, it feels so sweet
after all that.

42:45.772 --> 42:47.689
- I love the dimensions
of that blade.

42:47.732 --> 42:49.691
It's a great cutter.

42:49.734 --> 42:51.150
<i> When I was going through</i>
<i> that rope, it just went--</i>

42:51.194 --> 42:52.860
<i> [makes slicing sound]</i>
<i> Right through.</i>

42:52.904 --> 42:54.571
You definitely know
how to put an edge on something.

42:54.614 --> 42:57.031
- I feel like
I've completely redeemed myself.

42:57.075 --> 42:58.950
<i> It feels incredible.</i>

42:58.994 --> 43:00.493
<i> Like, I never thought</i>
<i> that the title,</i>

43:00.537 --> 43:02.120
<i> "Forged in Fire" champion,</i>

43:02.163 --> 43:03.580
would mean as much
as it does to me right now.

43:03.623 --> 43:07.959
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
